about.summary: A general-purpose computational engine for data analysis, drake rebuilds intermediate data objects when their dependencies change, and it skips work when the results are already up to date. Not every execution starts from scratch, there is native support for parallel and distributed computing, and completed projects have tangible evidence that they are reproducible. Extensive documentation, from beginner-friendly tutorials to practical examples and more, is available at the reference website <https://ropensci.github.io/drake/> and the online manual <https://ropenscilabs.github.io/drake-manual/>.

name: r-drake
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "7.11.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-drake
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/drake_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/drake/drake_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: f1fd2ef8e9e2c89553d7ad85521215dbe9f5bc58b62ea0a37ee8e46bff700b7a

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}  # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-base64url
    - r-digest
    - r-igraph
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-storr >=1.1.0
    - r-txtq >=0.1.3
    - r-vctrs >=0.2.0
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-base64url
    - r-digest
    - r-igraph
    - r-rlang >=0.2.0
    - r-storr >=1.1.0
    - r-txtq >=0.1.3
    - r-vctrs >=0.2.0

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('drake')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('drake')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://github.com/ropensci/drake
  license: GPL-3
  summary: A general-purpose computational engine for data analysis, drake rebuilds intermediate data objects when their dependencies change, and it skips work when
    the results are already up to date. Not every execution starts from scratch, there is native support for parallel and distributed computing, and completed projects
    have tangible evidence that they are reproducible. Extensive documentation, from beginner-friendly tutorials to practical examples and more, is available at the
    reference website <https://ropensci.github.io/drake/> and the online manual <https://ropenscilabs.github.io/drake-manual/>.
  license_family: GPL3
  license_file: {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-3

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
    - brendanf
    - wlandau
